Bangladesh,[a] officially the People's Republic of Bangladesh,[b] is
a country in South Asia. It is the eighth-most populous country in the
world and among the most densely populated with a population of over
171 million within an area of 148,460 square kilometres (57,320 sq mi).
Bangladesh shares land borders with India to the north, west, \ and east,
and Myanmar to the southeast. It has a coastline along the Bay of Bengal
to its south and is separated from Bhutan and Nepal by the Siliguri.
